<i>Make 'em laugh</i>

30:56.813 --> 30:58.014
Ready, Don?

30:58.106 --> 31:00.104
- All set.
- Here we go again.

31:00.108 --> 31:02.811
- We have another smash on our hands.
- I hope so.

31:02.861 --> 31:04.313
You're darn tooting we have.

31:04.321 --> 31:07.149
- Where's Lina?
- Here she is, Mr. Dexter.

31:07.199 --> 31:10.284
Well! Here comes our
lovely leading lady now.

31:10.285 --> 31:13.830
This wig weighs a ton. What
dope'd wear a thing like this?

31:13.831 --> 31:15.289
Everybody wore them.

31:15.290 --> 31:17.163
Then everybody was a dope.

31:17.167 --> 31:19.244
- You look beautiful.
- You look great.

31:19.252 --> 31:21.329
Let's get into the set.

31:21.838 --> 31:23.039
Thanks, Joe.

31:23.048 --> 31:27.128
I looked for you at Wally Ray's
party. Where were you?

31:27.135 --> 31:28.882
I've been busy.

31:28.929 --> 31:32.178
And I know what you've been
busy at. Looking for that girl.

31:32.182 --> 31:34.601
- As a matter of fact, yes.
- Why?

31:34.643 --> 31:36.095
I've been worried about her.

31:36.144 --> 31:38.267
You should've been
worried about me.

31:38.313 --> 31:41.392
I'm the one who got the
whipped cream in the kisser.

31:41.441 --> 31:44.064
Yes, but you didn't lose
your job, and she did.

31:44.069 --> 31:47.238
Darn tooting she did.
I arranged it.

31:47.239 --> 31:48.440
What?

31:48.448 --> 31:52.027
They weren't gonna fire her,
so I told them they better.

31:52.077 --> 31:53.950
- Why...
- Don, now remember.

31:53.954 --> 31:57.909
You're madly in love with her and
you have to overcome her shyness.

31:57.999 --> 32:00.952
Cosmo, mood music.

32:02.504 --> 32:04.081
Roll 'em!

32:05.424 --> 32:07.046
Okay, Don.

32:07.092 --> 32:08.464
Now enter.

32:09.511 --> 32:10.803
You see her.

32:10.846 --> 32:12.639
Run to her!

32:17.227 --> 32:21.182
Why, you rattlesnake, you.
You got that poor kid fired.

32:21.189 --> 32:25.394
That's not all I'm gonna do if
I ever get my hands on her.

32:25.444 --> 32:28.022
I never heard of anything so low.

32:28.029 --> 32:29.697
Fine. Fine. Looks great.

32:30.323 --> 32:32.070
What did you do it for?

32:32.117 --> 32:35.411
Because you liked her.
I could tell.

32:35.412 --> 32:37.080
So that's it.

32:37.122 --> 32:41.543
Believe me, I don't like her
half as much as I hate you.

32:41.585 --> 32:43.287
You reptile.

32:43.336 --> 32:46.289
Sticks and stones
may break my bones.

32:46.298 --> 32:48.592
I'd like to break every
bone in your body.

32:48.593 --> 32:51.090
You and who else, you big lummox?

32:51.470 --> 32:52.762
Now kiss her, Don.

32:54.389 --> 32:56.466
That's it. More.

32:56.475 --> 32:58.973
Great! Cut!

32:59.936 --> 33:04.312
You couldn't kiss me like that and not
mean it just a teensy-weensy bit.

33:04.316 --> 33:07.690
Meet the world's greatest actor.
I'd rather kiss a tarantula!

33:07.736 --> 33:09.813
- You don't mean that!
- I don't...?

33:09.863 --> 33:12.280
Joe, bring me a tarantula.
Now listen...

33:12.281 --> 33:15.159
Stop that chitchat, you lovebirds.
Let's get another take.

33:15.160 --> 33:16.407
Hold it.

33:16.578 --> 33:18.412
- Hold it, Dexter!
- Hello, Mr. Simpson.

33:18.413 --> 33:19.830
We're really rolling.

33:19.873 --> 33:22.326
Well, you can stop rolling at once.

33:22.334 --> 33:24.286
All right, everybody! Save it!

33:24.294 --> 33:27.168
Save it? Tell them to go home.
We're shutting down.

33:27.172 --> 33:28.965
Don't stand there. Tell them!

33:29.007 --> 33:31.759
Go home until further notice!
What is this?

33:31.760 --> 33:32.927
What's the matter?

33:32.928 --> 33:35.301
<i>The Jazz Singer</i>,
that's what's the matter.

33:35.305 --> 33:38.805
<i>Oh, my darling little mammy
Down in Alabamy</i>

33:38.808 --> 33:42.478
This is no joke. It's a sensation.
The public's screaming for more.

33:42.479 --> 33:45.022
- More what?
- Talking pictures.

33:45.023 --> 33:48.397
- It's just a freak.
- We should have such a freak.

33:48.401 --> 33:51.946
I said talking pictures were a
menace, but no one would listen.

33:51.947 --> 33:56.527
We're going to make <i>The Duelling
Cavalier</i> into a talking picture.

33:56.535 --> 33:58.487
That means I'm out of a job.

33:58.495 --> 34:00.496
I can start suffering and
write that symphony.

34:00.539 --> 34:03.413
We'll put you in as head
of the music department.

34:03.458 --> 34:06.626
Thanks. I can stop suffering
and write that symphony.

34:06.627 --> 34:09.581
Wait a second. Talking pictures!
You should wait...

34:09.589 --> 34:12.130
Every studio's jumping
on the bandwagon.

34:12.132 --> 34:14.882
All the theaters are putting
in sound equipment.

34:14.928 --> 34:16.596
We know nothing about it.

34:16.597 --> 34:18.389
What do you have to know?

34:18.389 --> 34:21.719
You do what you always did.
You just add talking to it.

34:21.810 --> 34:23.853
Believe me, it'll be a sensation.

34:24.020 --> 34:27.143
"Lamont and Lockwood. They talk!"

34:27.148 --> 34:30.522
Well, of course we talk.
Don't everybody?

34:47.668 --> 34:49.670
<i>I got a feeling
You're fooling</i>

34:49.670 --> 34:51.589
<i>I got a feeling
You're havin' fun</i>

34:51.630 --> 34:54.675
<i>I get the go-by
When you are done foolin' with me</i>

34:54.676 --> 34:57.720
<i>It's a holiday
Today's The Wedding of the Painted Doll</i>

34:58.346 --> 35:00.264
<i>It's a jolly day
The news is spreading</i>

