Kathy, come here.

38:49.744 --> 38:52.246
This will start a trend
in musical pictures.

38:52.247 --> 38:55.496
Mr. Simpson's thinking about
casting you as Zelda's sister.

38:55.500 --> 38:56.997
That's wonderful!

38:57.001 --> 38:58.453
Hey, Kathy!

38:58.586 --> 39:00.038
That's Kathy Selden.

39:00.088 --> 39:01.790
Thanks anyway. It was nice of you.

39:01.840 --> 39:03.917
- Wait a minute.
- That's all right.

39:03.925 --> 39:07.049
Before Mr. Lockwood refreshes your
memory, you may as well know...

39:07.095 --> 39:12.301
I'm the girl who hit Miss Lamont with
a cake. it was meant for Mr. Lockwood.

39:12.308 --> 39:14.556
Goodbye. I'm sorry.
I should've told you.

39:14.602 --> 39:16.850
Wait a minute.
What's this all about?

39:16.896 --> 39:20.396
We were gonna use her, but if
it'd make you and Lina unhappy...

39:20.441 --> 39:22.359
Unhappy? It's wonderful.

39:22.402 --> 39:24.104
He's been looking for her!

39:24.153 --> 39:25.855
Are you speaking for Lina also?

39:25.864 --> 39:29.113
The owner of the Coconut Grove
may do what Lina tells him...

39:29.117 --> 39:32.116
- ...but you're the head of this studio.
- Yes, I am.

39:32.120 --> 39:34.997
She's hired. Don't let Lina
know she's on the lot.

39:34.998 --> 39:36.199
Take care of that.

39:36.249 --> 39:37.496
Thank you, Mr. Simpson!

39:37.542 --> 39:41.497
I'm glad you turned up. We've been
looking inside every cake in town.

39:42.964 --> 39:45.258
Is it all right for you
to be seen with me?

39:45.259 --> 39:48.132
You mean, lofty star
with humble player?

39:48.177 --> 39:52.678
Not exactly. But for lunch, don't you
tear a pheasant with Miss Lamont?

39:52.682 --> 39:56.978
Look, Kathy. All that stuff about
Lina and me is sheer publicity.

39:57.020 --> 39:59.769
Oh? Certainly seems
more than that...

39:59.814 --> 40:03.191
from what I've read in all those
articles in the fan magazines.

40:03.192 --> 40:07.989
Ohh, you read the fan magazines?

40:08.031 --> 40:11.451
I pick them up in the beauty
parlor or the dentist's office...

40:11.452 --> 40:13.327
just like anybody.

40:13.328 --> 40:14.780
Honest?

40:16.497 --> 40:18.165
I buy four or five a month.

40:18.207 --> 40:19.875
You buy four or five...?

40:21.044 --> 40:23.121
To get back to the main point...

40:23.171 --> 40:26.250
you achieve a kind of intimacy
in all your pictures...

40:26.257 --> 40:29.176
Did you say all my pictures?

40:31.346 --> 40:34.425
Now that I think of it,
I've seen eight or nine of them.

40:34.474 --> 40:35.675
Eight or nine.

40:35.725 --> 40:38.599
It seems to me
I remember someone saying:

40:38.686 --> 40:42.106
"If you've seen one,
you've seen them all."

40:43.608 --> 40:46.903
I did say some awful things
that night, didn't I?

40:47.195 --> 40:49.818
No, I deserved them.

40:49.822 --> 40:53.572
Of course, I must admit I was
pretty much upset by them.

40:53.952 --> 40:59.204
So upset that I haven't been able to
think of anything but you ever since.

40:59.916 --> 41:01.413
Honest?

41:02.543 --> 41:03.995
Honest.

41:05.463 --> 41:08.548
Well, I've been pretty upset too.

41:08.549 --> 41:10.126
Kathy...

41:10.134 --> 41:12.177
Kathy, look, I...

41:12.220 --> 41:15.048
Kathy, seeing you
again now that I...

41:18.768 --> 41:21.938
I'm trying to say something
to you, but I...

41:21.980 --> 41:23.807
I'm such a ham.

41:23.815 --> 41:26.733
I guess I'm not able to
without the proper setting.

41:26.734 --> 41:27.901
What do you mean?

41:27.902 --> 41:29.445
Well...

41:30.571 --> 41:32.148
Come here.

41:40.331 --> 41:42.579
This is the proper setting.

41:43.626 --> 41:45.499
Why, it's just an empty stage.

41:45.545 --> 41:47.292
At first glance, yes.

41:47.338 --> 41:49.040
But wait a second.

41:50.800 --> 41:53.219
A beautiful sunset.

41:56.097 --> 41:59.050
Mist from the distant mountains.

42:00.977 --> 42:03.475
Colored lights in a garden.

42:05.606 --> 42:10.733
Milady is standing on her balcony,
in a rose-trellised bower...

42:14.365 --> 42:16.408
flooded with moonlight.

42:16.451 --> 42:20.030
We add 500,000
kilowatts of stardust.

42:23.207 --> 42:25.751
A soft summer breeze.

42:26.753 --> 42:28.421
And...

42:29.088 --> 42:31.757
You sure look lovely
in the moonlight.

42:33.134 --> 42:37.214
Now that you have the proper
setting, can you say it?

42:39.140 --> 42:40.387
<i>I'll try.</i>

42:41.809 --> 42:44.637
<i>Life was a song</i>

42:44.937 --> 42:48.016
<i>You came along</i>

42:48.024 --> 42:53.355
<i>I've laid awake the
whole night through</i>

42:54.614 --> 42:57.158
<i>If I but dared</i>

42:57.825 --> 43:00.369
<i>To think you cared</i>

43:00.870 --> 43:02.913
<i>This is what</i>

43:03.164 --> 43:07.540
<i>I'd say to you</i>

43:10.171 --> 43:14.968
<i>You were meant for me</i>

43:18.346 --> 43:23.177
<i>And I was meant for you</i>

43:26.479 --> 43:29.933
<i>Nature patterned you</i>

43:30.191 --> 43:33.565
<i>And when she was done</i>

43:34.529 --> 43:38.450
<i>You were all the sweet things</i>

43:39.242 --> 43:42.286
<i>Rolled up in one</i>

43:42.495 --> 43:44.368
<i>You're like</i>

43:44.372 --> 43:49.578
<i>A plaintive melody</i>

43:52.380 --> 43:57.711
<i>That never lets me free</i>

44:00.721 --> 44:04.141
<i>But I'm content</i>

44:04.892 --> 44:08.847
<i>The angels must have sent you</i>

44:09.605 --> 44:13.435
<i>And they meant you</i>

44:14.443 --> 44:17.772
<i>Just for me</i>

45:44.492 --> 45:48.697
<i>But I'm content</i>

45:49.789 --> 45:54.836
<i>The angels must have sent you</i>

45:55.419 --> 46:01.046
<i>And they meant you</i>

46:02.009 --> 46:06.715
<i>Just for me</i>

46:25.616 --> 46:27.068
Now...

46:27.118 --> 46:32.040
Ta, te, ti, toe, too.

46:32.957 --> 46:37.458
Ta, te, ti, toe, too.

46:37.461 --> 46:38.958
No, no, Miss Lamont...

46:39.046 --> 46:42.250
round tones, round tones.

46:42.300 --> 46:45.595
Now let me hear you read your line.

46:46.304 --> 46:49.132
"And I can't stan' 'im."

46:49.181 --> 46:52.180
And I can't stand him.

46:52.226 --> 46:55.600
"And I can't stan' 'im."

46:55.771 --> 46:57.268
"Can't."

46:57.356 --> 46:58.808
Can't.

46:59.567 --> 47:01.860
"Can't."

47:01.861 --> 47:04.155
Can't!

47:04.322 --> 47:06.865
Can't. Can't.

47:06.866 --> 47:08.318
Very good.

47:08.326 --> 47:11.700
"Around the rocks the
rugged rascal ran."

47:11.746 --> 47:13.539
"Around the rocks the rugged..."

47:13.581 --> 47:16.079
No, no. "Rocks." "Rocks."

47:16.125 --> 47:18.626
"Around the rocks the
rugged rascal ran."

47:18.627 --> 47:19.828
Very good.

47:19.837 --> 47:21.004
Hi, Don.

47:21.005 --> 47:23.128
- Shall I continue?
- Don't mind me.

47:23.132 --> 47:26.677
Now. "Sinful Caesar
sipped his snifter..."

47:26.719 --> 47:29.843
"seized his knees and sneezed."

47:29.889 --> 47:32.342
"Sinful Caesar snipped
his sifter..."

47:32.391 --> 47:33.683
Sipped his snifter.

47:33.684 --> 47:35.807
"Sipped his snifter."

47:35.811 --> 47:37.137
Oh, thank you.

47:37.188 --> 47:41.689
"Sinful Caesar sipped his snifter,
seized his knees and sneezed."

47:41.692 --> 47:43.644
- Marvelous.
- Wonderful.

47:43.652 --> 47:45.695
Here is a good one.

47:45.738 --> 47:49.442
"Chester chooses chestnuts, cheddar
cheese with chewy chives."

47:49.450 --> 47:51.573
"He chews them and he chooses them."

47:51.619 --> 47:53.867
"He chooses them and
he chews them..."

47:53.871 --> 47:56.915
"those chestnuts, cheddar
cheese and chives..."

47:56.916 --> 47:59.414
"...in cheery, charming chunks."

47:59.460 --> 48:02.379
- Wonderful! Do another one.
- Thank you.

48:02.838 --> 48:05.882
"Moses supposes his
toeses are roses..."

48:05.925 --> 48:08.802
"but Moses supposes erroneously."

48:08.803 --> 48:11.506
"Moses, he knowses his
toeses aren't roses..."

48:11.555 --> 48:15.055
"...as Moses supposes
his toeses to be."

48:18.229 --> 48:20.932
"Moses supposes his
toeses are roses..."

48:20.981 --> 48:23.525
"but Moses supposes erroneously."

48:23.567 --> 48:26.771
"But Moses, he knowses
his toes aren't roses..."

48:26.821 --> 48:29.490
"as Moses supposes
his toeses to be."

48:29.532 --> 48:32.201
Moses supposes his
toeses are roses...

48:32.243 --> 48:34.786
but Moses supposes erroneously.

48:34.787 --> 48:36.204
A mose is a mose.

48:36.205 --> 48:37.531
A rose is a rose.

48:37.540 --> 48:39.242
A toes is a toes.

48:40.584 --> 48:43.037
<i>Moses supposes his toeses are roses</i>

48:43.087 --> 48:45.915
<i>But Moses supposes erroneously</i>

48:45.965 --> 48:48.668
<i>Moses, he knowses
His toeses aren't roses</i>

48:48.717 --> 48:51.796
<i>As Moses supposes his toeses to be</i>

48:51.804 --> 48:54.472
<i>Moses supposes his toeses are roses</i>

48:54.473 --> 48:56.891
<i>But Moses supposes erroneously</i>

48:56.892 --> 48:59.720
<i>For Moses knowses
His toeses aren't roses</i>

48:59.770 --> 49:02.814
<i>As Moses supposes his toeses to be</i>

49:02.815 --> 49:05.438
<i>A rose is a rose
Is a rose is a rose is</i>

49:05.484 --> 49:08.278
<i>A rose is what Moses
Supposes his toes is</i>

49:08.320 --> 49:10.943
<i>Couldn't be a lily
Or a taffy daffy dilly</i>

49:10.948 --> 49:13.901
<i>It's gotta be a rose
'Cause it rhymes with "mose"</i>

49:13.951 --> 49:15.403
<i>Moses</i>

49:16.412 --> 49:17.909
<i>Moses</i>

49:18.956 --> 49:20.533
<i>Moses</i>

51:19.326 --> 51:21.528
<i>"A"</i>

51:27.501 --> 51:29.453
All right, here we go.

51:29.503 --> 51:31.713
- Quiet!
- Quiet.

51:31.714 --> 51:33.336
Roll 'em!

51:35.968 --> 51:39.047
<i>Oh, Pierre.
You shouldn't have come.</i>

51:39.096 --> 51:43.176
She's gotta talk into the mike.
I can't pick it up.

51:44.101 --> 51:45.553
Cut!

51:45.561 --> 51:46.933
What's the matter?

51:46.937 --> 51:48.184
It's Lina.

51:48.230 --> 51:51.559
Look, Lina, don't you
remember? I told you.

51:51.609 --> 51:54.562
There's a microphone right there...

51:54.612 --> 51:57.113
- ...in the bush.
- Yeah.

51:57.114 --> 51:59.237
You have to talk into it.

51:59.283 --> 52:01.861
I was talking.
Wasn't I, Miss Dinsmore?

52:01.869 --> 52:06.119
Yes, my dear. But please
remember, round tones.

52:06.123 --> 52:09.623
"Pierre, you shouldn't have come."

52:09.668 --> 52:12.166
Pierre, you shouldn't have come.

52:12.212 --> 52:13.584
That's much better...

52:13.589 --> 52:15.506
Hold it a second.

52:15.507 --> 52:17.425
Now, Lina, look.

52:17.426 --> 52:18.843
Here's the mike.

52:18.886 --> 52:21.304
Right here in the bush.

52:21.305 --> 52:22.513
Yeah.

52:22.514 --> 52:24.216
Now, you talk towards it.

52:24.266 --> 52:27.470
The sound goes through
the cable to the box.

52:27.519 --> 52:31.349
A man records it on a
big record in wax...

52:31.398 --> 52:35.273
but you have to talk
into the mike first.

52:35.277 --> 52:36.774
In the bush!

52:36.820 --> 52:38.317
Now try it again.

52:38.405 --> 52:39.652
Gee, this is dumb.

52:39.657 --> 52:41.951
She'll get it, Dexter. Don't worry.

52:41.992 --> 52:45.321
We're all nervous the first day.
Everything will be okay.

52:45.412 --> 52:48.115
By the way. You know the
scene coming up where I say:

52:48.123 --> 52:50.246
"imperious princess of the night"?

52:50.250 --> 52:54.045
I don't like those lines. Is it all
right if I say what I always do?

52:54.046 --> 52:56.749
"I love you. I love you.
I love you."

52:56.799 --> 52:59.252
Sure. Any way it's comfortable.

52:59.259 --> 53:00.968
But into the bush!

53:00.969 --> 53:02.178
Okay.

53:02.179 --> 53:03.426
Again!

53:03.430 --> 53:04.973
Quiet!

53:05.140 --> 53:06.717
Roll 'em!

53:19.071 --> 53:20.318
Cut!

53:20.572 --> 53:22.866
We're missing every other word.

53:22.950 --> 53:25.369
You've got to talk into the mike!

53:25.452 --> 53:28.030
Well, I can't make love to a bush!

53:28.080 --> 53:30.328
All right, all right.

53:30.749 --> 53:34.328
We'll have to think
of something else.

53:39.717 --> 53:41.214
What are you doing?

53:41.260 --> 53:43.929
- You're being wired for sound.
- What?

53:43.971 --> 53:48.051
Watch out for those dentalized
D's and T's and those flat A's.

53:48.058 --> 53:50.393
Everybody's picking on me.

53:50.394 --> 53:51.644
Okay, Lina.

53:51.645 --> 53:54.098
Now look at this flower, see?

53:54.148 --> 53:56.191
The mike is in there.

53:56.650 --> 53:58.102
That's it.

53:58.110 --> 54:01.029
The sound will run from it...

54:01.280 --> 54:04.073
through this wire, onto the record.

54:04.074 --> 54:06.402
It'll catch whatever you say.

54:06.410 --> 54:09.784
Now let's hear how it sounds, Lina.

54:10.038 --> 54:12.457
Okay, quiet!

54:12.499 --> 54:14.076
Roll 'em!

54:16.712 --> 54:19.006
<i>Oh, Pierre,
you shouldn't have come.</i>

54:20.299 --> 54:22.718
<i>You're flirting with danger.</i>

54:23.761 --> 54:24.962
What's that noise?

54:25.012 --> 54:26.964
It's picking up her heartbeat.

54:27.014 --> 54:28.716
Swell.

54:29.433 --> 54:30.725
Cut!

54:34.813 --> 54:37.266
That's right. That should do it.

54:37.316 --> 54:38.938
Now, don't forget.

54:38.942 --> 54:41.144
The mike is on your shoulder.

54:41.195 --> 54:45.025
And whatever you say goes through
the wire onto the record.

54:45.073 --> 54:48.322
Now, please, Lina,
talk into the mike.

54:48.368 --> 54:51.868
Don't make any quick movements
or you might disconnect it.

54:51.914 --> 54:53.582
Okay, let's go.

54:53.624 --> 54:55.708
- Quiet.
- Quiet.

54:55.709 --> 54:57.536
Roll 'em.

55:00.547 --> 55:04.801
Oh, Pierre, you shouldn't have come.
You're flirting with danger.

55:04.802 --> 55:07.425
What's this wire doing here?
It's dangerous.

55:21.902 --> 55:23.820
You'd better not go in together.

55:23.862 --> 55:26.941
Lina's probably waiting
right inside the door.

55:26.990 --> 55:29.033
- Oh, how I wish...
- Don't worry.

55:29.076 --> 55:32.780
I'll lead the cheering section
in the balcony. Good luck.

55:37.417 --> 55:39.915
- Mr. Lockwood.
- Hello.

56:08.031 --> 56:10.108
What's that? The storm outside?

56:10.158 --> 56:12.827
It's those pearls, Mr. Simpson.

56:17.875 --> 56:22.421
<i>I am the noblest lady of the court,
second only to the queen.</i>

56:22.462 --> 56:26.337
<i>Yet I am the saddest
of mortals in France.</i>

56:26.383 --> 56:28.426
<i>What is the matter, milady?</i>

56:28.468 --> 56:30.841
<i>I'm so downhearted, Theresa.</i>

56:30.888 --> 56:34.388
<i>My father has me betrothed
to the Baron de Landsfield...</i>

56:34.433 --> 56:36.101
<i>and I can't stand him.</i>

56:37.269 --> 56:38.891
<i>Oh, but he's such a catch.</i>

56:38.937 --> 56:42.732
<i>All the ladies of the court
wish they were in your shoes.</i>

56:42.774 --> 56:45.602
<i>My heart belongs to another...</i>

56:46.153 --> 56:48.276
<i>Pierre de Bataille.</i>

56:48.280 --> 56:52.451
<i>Ever since I met him, I can't
get him out of my mind.</i>

56:52.534 --> 56:55.203
Sounds good and loud, huh?

57:03.253 --> 57:04.670
<i>Oh, Pierre!</i>

57:06.089 --> 57:09.213
<i>You shouldn't have come.
You're flirting with danger.</i>

57:09.301 --> 57:11.720
<i>They will surely find you out.</i>

57:11.803 --> 57:14.756
<i>Your head is much too valuable.</i>

57:14.806 --> 57:18.184
She never could remember
where the microphone was.

57:18.185 --> 57:21.104
<i>'Tis Cupid himself
that called me here...</i>

57:21.188 --> 57:22.731
<i>and I...</i>

57:22.856 --> 57:25.684
<i>smitten by his arrow,
must fly to your side...</i>

57:27.527 --> 57:30.571
<i>despite the threats
of Madame Guillotine.</i>

57:31.198 --> 57:34.242
<i>But the night is
full of our enemies.</i>

57:37.663 --> 57:40.116
What you hitting him
with, a blackjack?

57:40.999 --> 57:43.542
<i>Imperious princess of the night...</i>

57:43.543 --> 57:45.086
<i>I love you.</i>

57:45.170 --> 57:46.917
<i>Oh, Pierre.</i>

57:46.922 --> 57:48.749
<i>I love you.</i>

57:48.799 --> 57:53.219
<i>I love you, I love you, I love you,
I love you, I love you.</i>

57:53.220 --> 57:57.596
<i>I love you, I love you,
I love you, I love you!</i>

57:59.393 --> 58:01.937
Did somebody get paid
for writing that?

58:04.898 --> 58:06.565
Sounds like a comedy.

58:06.566 --> 58:09.235
- It's a Lockwood-Lamont talkie.
- What?

58:09.236 --> 58:10.938
This is terrible.

58:18.036 --> 58:19.283
What's that?

58:19.329 --> 58:21.748
The sound. It's out
of synchronization!

58:21.749 --> 58:23.245
Tell them to fix it.

58:23.250 --> 58:24.952
Yes, sir.

58:26.253 --> 58:27.753
<i>What's this? Yvonne?</i>

58:27.754 --> 58:31.382
<i>Captured by Rouge Noir
of the Purple Terror?</i>

58:31.383 --> 58:34.132
<i>Ohh. Oh, my sword!</i>

58:34.136 --> 58:36.805
<i>I must fly to her side!</i>

58:36.847 --> 58:39.141
<i>Yvonne, Yvonne...</i>

58:39.266 --> 58:40.968
<i>my own.</i>

58:41.435 --> 58:44.935
<i>Pierre will save me. Pierre!</i>

58:44.938 --> 58:48.267
<i>Pierre is miles away, you witch.</i>

58:48.650 --> 58:50.568
<i>No, no, no.</i>

58:50.569 --> 58:52.778
<i>Yes, yes, yes.</i>

58:52.779 --> 58:54.652
<i>No, no, no.</i>

58:54.656 --> 58:57.655
<i>Yes, yes, yes.</i>

59:04.082 --> 59:05.374
This is a scream.

59:05.417 --> 59:06.994
Give me pictures like
<i>The Jazz Singer.</i>

59:07.002 --> 59:09.375
"I love you, I love you,
I love you"...

59:11.798 --> 59:14.966
- We're ruined. We're all ruined.
- You can't release this picture.

59:14.967 --> 59:18.388
We're booked to open in six
weeks all over the country.

59:18.472 --> 59:21.599
But you're such big stars,
we might get by.

59:21.600 --> 59:23.802
I never wanna see Lockwood
and Lamont again.

59:23.810 --> 59:25.011
Wasn't it awful?

59:25.020 --> 59:27.689
This is the worst
picture ever made.

59:27.773 --> 59:29.646
I liked it.

59:37.783 --> 59:40.202
Well, take a last look at it.

59:40.285 --> 59:42.533
It'll be up for auction
in the morning.

59:42.537 --> 59:44.159
You're out of your mind.

59:44.164 --> 59:47.117
It's Saturday. No bank will
foreclose until Monday.

59:47.167 --> 59:49.836
- It wasn't so bad.
- That's what I told him.

59:50.170 --> 59:51.872
There's no use kidding myself.

59:51.963 --> 59:56.168
Once they release <i>The Duelling Cavalier</i>,
Lockwood and Lamont are through.

59:56.176 --> 59:58.174
The picture's a museum piece.

59:58.178 --> 59:59.755
I'm a museum piece.

59:59.805 --> 01:00:02.679
Things went wrong with
the sound. Get the technical...

